import React from 'react';

const SvgGraphic = () => {
    return (
        <svg width="600" height="400" viewBox="0 0 600 400" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <g id="group">
                <path id="triangle" d="M100 100 L500 150 L400 300 Z" fill="#FF5252"/>
                <text id="left-text" x="50" y="150" fill="white" font-family="Arial" font-size="16" transform="rotate(-45 50,150)">
                    Achievements
                </text>
                <text x="50" y="170" fill="white" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" transform="rotate(-45 50,170)">
                    Best Finance App On Playstore
                </text>
                <text id="right-text" x="450" y="130" fill="white" font-family="Arial" font-size="16" transform="rotate(45 450,130)">
                    Finance
                </text>
                <text x="450" y="150" fill="white" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" transform="rotate(45 450,150)">
                    Most Popular Accounting App
                </text>
                <rect id="bottom-rect" x="400" y="300" width="150" height="50" fill="#FF5252"/>
                <text id="bottom-text" x="425" y="330" fill="white" font-family="Arial" font-size="16">
                    Uifry Premium
                </text>
                <text x="425" y="350" fill="white" font-family="Arial" font-size="12">
                    Free Trial
                </text>
            </g>
        </svg>
    );
};

export default SvgGraphic;
